{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:53:50.724390+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've thoroughly reviewed the issue and the repository structure. Unfortunately, **all write operations** (file creation, file update, and bulk push) are being rejected with a `403 Resource not accessible by personal access token` error. The token I'm using only has read access to this repository, so I cannot commit the changes directly.\n\nHowever, I've completed all the analysis work and have the complete solution ready. Here's exactly what needs to be done:\n\n---\n\n## Issue #1 Summary: Add authentication API docs\n\n### Change 1: Create `docs/api/authentication.md` (new file)\n\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nAll API requests must include a valid access token.\n\n## Bearer Token\n\nPass the token in the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <your_token>\n```\n\n## Obtaining a Token\n\nRequest a token by sending a `POST` request to the `/auth/token` endpoint with your client credentials:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"client_id\": \"your_client_id\",\n  \"client_secret\": \"your_client_secret\"\n}\n```\n\nA successful response returns a JSON object containing the access token and its expiry:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJ...\",\n  \"token_type\": \"Bearer\",\n  \"expires_in\": 3600\n}\n```\n\n## Token Expiry\n\nTokens expire after the duration specified in `expires_in` (in seconds). Request a new token before the current one expires to avoid `401 Unauthorized` responses.\n\n## Error Responses\n\nIf authentication fails, the API returns a standard error object. See [Errors](errors.md) for details.\n```\n\n### Change 2: Update `mkdocs.yml` (add Authentication to nav)\n\nThe `API:` section in the `nav:` block needs a new entry between `Overview` and `Errors`:\n\n```yaml\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md    # ← new line\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\n### Validation\n\nThe `Makefile` runs `python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`, which checks:\n- Required files exist (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `mkdocs.yml`, `requirements.txt`, `docs/index.md`)\n- `mkdocs.yml` defines `site_name:` and `nav:`\n\nBoth new and updated files satisfy these checks, so the validation command (`make validate`) will continue to pass.\n\n---\n\n**Limitation:** I was unable to write the files to the repository due to the personal access token lacking write permissions (all push attempts returned HTTP 403). A maintainer with write access would need to apply these two changes manually, or the token permissions would need to be expanded.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 613, "prompt_tokens": 12317, "total_tokens": 12930, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 48, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10944, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0011699634, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0006366534, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00053331}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780865619-GfL5jLXQyakd1WGJULAu", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3dc-d449-7730-be89-6d97479d0035-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12317, "output_tokens": 613, "total_tokens": 12930, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 10944}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 48}}}}]}}}
